This command is using the SSH (Secure Shell) protocol to connect to a remote server at the IP address ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com. The -i option specifies the identity file to use for authentication, which in this case is "~/UserKey.pem". The -C option enables compression of data during the connection.

The -L option specifies a local port forwarding, which means that any incoming connections on port 25900 on the local machine will be forwarded to port 5900 on the remote server. This allows you to access services running on the remote server as if they were running locally on your machine.

In summary, this command is connecting to a remote server using SSH and setting up a local port forwarding so that you can access services running on the remote server as if they were running locally on your machine.
